</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#778899><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/usammyd11.showPublicProfile?language=EN>sammyd11</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Disciple</span><br>  Posts: 251<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(11/26/01 7:45:29 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hmm</span><hr size=1> 1) Content - I think this is the biggest thing.  I play a Nightshade in Hibernia, and 2 weeks into the game, I'd been through 3 of 5 dungeons completely (Muire, Spragg, and Money Dungeon 1).  And they aren't really dungeons, just 8 connected rooms with no real design or anything of interest.  Add to that 2 dungeons have no items, and it gets kinda weak.  <br>
<br>
Several tradeskills aren't in, rogues aren't finished, many skills that were promised aren't added yet (climbing, disguises, etc.)  They just didn't get enough in before they released it.  In the spring with the expansion, it will be what it should have been at release imho.<br>
<br>
2)  Broadcast - No one uses the lfg channels, especially above lv20.  It's 10 times harder to find a group in DAoC than in EQ.  This can be very frustrating.  I miss /shout badly.<br>
<br>
3) Grouping is the *only* good way to get exp.  Unless you are a solo class and gimp yourself for group and RvR (like a druid ignoring heal and putting all points into pet), grouping will bring exp 5 times as fast as soloing.  Granted, I am a Nightshade, but I can solo high blues very easily with no risk of death with 30% endurance and half health left.  Even then, the exp is so slow that its pointless.  It's better to run around for 2 hours lfg and getting in one for an hour than to solo for 3 hours.  That would be fine if they had a good way to find a group, but as it is, it gets very frustrating.<br>
<br>
I would be willing to go from one end of the realm to another to group, but my lfg flag won't show up way up there, so they will never know I'm looking.  Also, lfg flags don't show up in dungeons, which is exactly where you are trying to go to half the time.<br>
<br>
4) Mob aggro is brilliant.  Very interesting, and good improvement, although my one complaint is there is no skill to pulling anymore.  You get a number of mobs based on your parties strength, so who cares which mob you tag?<br>
<br>
5)  Travel I think is fine.  Bards and wardens can make you run fast, and you are never more than a 30 second run from a horse.  You can jump off a horse and catch another one to get exactly where you need to be.  Very rarely do I need more than 2 horses, so its only 10s.<br>
<br>
6)  RvR I have problems with.  If you get in a raid, or in a group defending against a raid, it's fun, but that doesn't happen a lot, and its a crapshoot whether you will get in one.  If you go solo or with a single group to raid, half the time you die to a mob and have to release with exp loss and never even see another player.  If you get to other players, half the time they are purple and you all die in one shot, and the other half the time they are grey, and you kill them all for 5 rps total.  About once a year you find an even con group and have a good fight.  They need to fix this so that there is a much quicker, easier way to get in fights with people your level. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/ugarouin.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Garouin</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Monk</span><br>  Posts: 173<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(11/26/01 1:45:43 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Hmm</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> They need to fix this so that there is a much quicker, easier way to get in fights with people your level.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
