       Why did it blow? Well, the main reason was that it was very lonely.  For all I knew, I would have been paying 10 dollars a month to play by myself.  I mean I was surprised to not hear crickets churping in my speakers, or see a tumble weed go across the screen.  No OOC, no SHOUT, no AUCTION, and even though there is BROADCAST, you can only use it in town. Which brings me to my next point.<br>
      I couldn't even go into a town and hit any of my arrow keys without doing a full 90 degree turn.  Framerate was that bad.  No joke.  And I'll be the first to admit the computer I have is out of date, but from what I've read people with better computers than mine were having trouble too.  I don't know maybe they've fixed that by now.<br>
      Anyway to wrap this up (so that the avid fans of DAoC can flame away), DAoC is a poor interpretation of EQ and it bites.  Why play DAoC with it's 10 or so dungeons when you can play EQ, which I'm sure has close to, if not over, 100 zones.  Maybe, in a couple of years, I'll play it again to see if it's any better, but that's only if it's still around by then.<br>
<br>
P.S.  Yeah I know I was harsh on the game, but maybe someone who plays EQ will read this and save 50 dollars + 10 more a month.  Just my opinion. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/udailyn.showPublicProfile?language=EN>dailyn</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(3/5/02 3:52:46 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: It's been five weeks, how does DAoC rate now?</span><hr size=1> Just to throw in my couple cents on this topic.  I played EQ for a year and a half before DAOC came out and decided that RvR sounded like a blast.  Played camelot for 4 months and am now back playin EQ.  Camelot rocks if you are new to this type of game.  Leveling is simple, death is relatively painless, and getting decent equipment is not a monumental task.  You can solo pretty well with most classes and most classes have something to bring to a group.  The downside is that if you are an experienced player things can get old quickly.  The world is much smaller and there is simply less to explore and do.  It was fun for awhile, but lacked a challenge and really lacked substance imho.  RvR was alot of fun for awhile, but even that got old.  Most battles were simply hack at the nearest enemy and wait for a rez.  With 100 realmmates running through Albion, fort taking became virtually risk free and simply a matter of wacking on the gates for 15 minutes then taking 3 to kill all the npc defenders inside.  Now before folks start telling me I don't know what I'm talking about, I did rvr extensively.  My chars are not low level.  After mudding for years, then playing EQ for a couple,  Camelot just didn't do it for me.  I must confess though, I'm much more impressed with Mythic as far as willingness to work with players to improve the game than I am with Verant.<br>
