<br>
The problem for me was it seemed like a much more pro-casual environment. Everyone in the same class tends to have the same equipment, just dyed a different color. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#cccccc><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub38.ezboard.com/bmonklybusiness43508.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=sanity>Sanity</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Young Grasshoppah</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#8b1a1a>(4/30/02 11:48:26 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: DAOC</span><hr size=1> I played EQ for 6 months, DAOC for 5, and AO for 2, and now I'm back to EQ and loving it.<br>
<br>
I think the lack of high-end content other than RvR is why I left. Hey, if RvR is your bag then that's great. I thought it would be mine too, but it isn't. It seems mostly pointless in that victories and losses in RvR don't really affect the way you play the game day-to-day.<br>
<br>
My opinion is that they should set up a special server that completely redoes zone boundaries between the home realms and the frontier realms. Instead of making the frontier gate fortress the only point of entrance into an enemy's home realm, make it just a large, well-defended castle with a decently sized force whose job it is to patrol the whole border area. That way large parties could sneak into the home realms and wreak havok.<br>
<br>
If the idea of massive PvP battles as the be-all-end-all turns you off, then DAOC is not for you. Once you get to level 40 (the level at which I quit), you will have, in my experience, explored every nook and cranny of every zone that you could possibly visit (without cheating and sneaking into the enemy homerealms, theoretically supposed to be impossible). In 44 levels in EQ I have maybe explored 1/4 of the game.<br>
<br>
The one gut feeling that I missed the most in DAOC was the feeling that I was immersed in an absolutely vast and immense world. Norrath is king as far as sheer size and amount of content is concerned. Yes, quality should win out over quantity, but in EQ's case, <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> variety</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> is king. There are so many different areas, with so many different pulling strategies required. So many ways to die. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  DAOC is rather boring as far as this goes. The first xp group you join in DAOC will work more-or-less the same as an xp group that you will be in when you ding 50.<br>
<br>
The thing is, there needs to be a more tangible reward for putting in the amount of time needed to get to level 50 in DAOC, because the content is exhausted so quickly. EQ seems to have perfected this because of all the high-level loot that is available, although I'm sure that there are people who are bored with EQ because they have &quot;seen it all&quot;.<br>
<br>
Anyway, it's really in the eye of the beholder. I think that you are going to choose the game that rewards you the most psychologically, and EQ happens to be that game for me. =) <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top">  Page <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.showMessageRange?topicID=209.topic&start=1&stop=20>1</a> <b>2</b>  </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.showPrevMessage?topicID=209.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.showNextMessage?topicID=209.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.emailToFriend?topicID=209.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.threadControl?topicID=209.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=209.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notification of replies<br>  <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fmonklybusiness43508frm14.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=209.topic>Unsubscribe</a> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies<br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub35.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</b><select name=forumName><option value="monklybusiness43508frm13">Board Rules<option value="monklybusiness43508frm17">Monk Change<option value="monklybusiness43508frm1">General<option value="monklybusines